## Overview
Miro is a web-based collaborative whiteboard platform designed for remote teams to brainstorm, plan, and work together.

## Purpose
Miro boards are valuable in R&D for visual collaboration, remote brainstorming, centralized idea capture, building on ideas, and project organization.

## How it works
Teams use Miro boards to add sticky notes, mind maps, drawings, images, and documents. Real-time editing allows everyone to see changes as they happen. Pre-built templates are available for common tasks like brainstorming sessions and user journey maps.

## Requirements
To effectively use Miro for R&D, teams need a clear focus on the objective, facilitation skills, balance between creativity and feasibility, documentation and version control, security and access control, and integration with other tools.

## Reflections
When using Miro for R&D purposes, it's essential to maintain a clear goal, balance creative ideas with practicality, document decisions, and track changes. Limiting access to authorized personnel is also crucial when dealing with sensitive information.
